arfaoui","cleared":false,"url":"/ala_arfaoui","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/018/291/ca82a894c15797b4c4adfebde519aaec1cb23776_original.jpg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":965844,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"","markdown_message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-05-20T03:08:51.250Z","updated_at":"2016-05-20T03:09:11.042Z","actor":{"username":"ala_arfaoui","cleared":false,"url":"/ala_arfaoui","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/018/291/ca82a894c15797b4c4adfebde519aaec1cb23776_original.jpg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false}],"activity_page_count":1,"activity_page_number":1,"summaries":[{"id":1965,"category":"team","content":"Our e-mail provider at the time had problems where some e-mails would not be sent out over TLS. Based on data from [Google Postmaster Tools](https://postmaster.google.com/), we were seeing as high as 12% of our e-mail from our provider to Google mail servers not encrypted. We opened a case with them on March 31st, 2016, about this issue, as this was something we couldn't directly control or fix.\n\nBased on this issue and some other issues we were having, we made the decision to migrate to a new e-mail provider for our e-mail. Since migrating in April 2016, we haven't seen any problems at all with sending our production e-mail over TLS to other mail servers, with 99.9%+ of our e-mail to Google's mail servers encrypted.\n\nOn May 17th, 2016, we received notification that the old provider has corrected the issue, though there are no current plans to migrate back.","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eOur e-mail provider at the time had problems where some e-mails would not be sent out over TLS. Based on data from \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpostmaster.google.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eGoogle Postmaster Tools\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, we were seeing as high as 12% of our e-mail from our provider to Google mail servers not encrypted. We opened a case with them on March 31st, 2016, about this issue, as this was something we couldn\u0026#39;t directly control or fix.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBased on this issue and some other issues we were having, we made the decision to migrate to a new e-mail provider for our e-mail. Since migrating in April 2016, we haven\u0026#39;t seen any problems at all with sending our production e-mail over TLS to other mail servers, with 99.9%+ of our e-mail to Google\u0026#39;s mail servers encrypted.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn May 17th, 2016, we received notification that the old provider has corrected the issue, though there are no current plans to migrate back.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"id":1659,"category":"researcher","content":"The vulnerability is that HackerOne Emails are sent in clear-text instead of TLS which is so vulnerable since any Man-in-the-middle attacker is able to read these sensitive Emails and **get**:\n * Password-reset links Emails **---\u003e Account Take over**\n * Private bug bounty programs names and activies **--\u003eInformation Disclosure**\n * Other private informations such as comments, support etc.. **--\u003eInformation Disclosure**","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe vulnerability is that HackerOne Emails are sent in clear-text instead of TLS which is so vulnerable since any Man-in-the-middle attacker is able to read these sensitive Emails and \u003cstrong\u003eget\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePassword-reset links Emails \u003cstrong\u003e---\u0026gt; Account Take over\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrivate bug bounty programs names and activies \u003cstrong\u003e--\u0026gt;Information Disclosure\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOther private informations such as comments, support etc.. \u003cstrong\u003e--\u0026gt;Information Disclosure\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n"}]}